user_request: A poem about a road not taken and the difference it made.
final_poem:
In paths untrodden, under skies of gray  
I find myself lost within my own dismayed array;   
A fork in time's relentless march lay before me grand – a choice to make or break it all:    
To take the road less walked on this land. 

Yet here I stand, paralyzed by fear’ endlessly swings  
The weight of impending decisions clinks and rings;   
A chasm divides where once stood a single tree – now two diverging roads lay bare within my eyes:    
One path leads to uncertainty. 

I hesitate, then choose the lesser known route ahead with quiet resolve in heart  
As weaved through each bygone year’s silent strife and art;   
A different road beckons – one of untold promise filled potential:    
My decision felt like a betrayal. 
Today, this choice has gifted me time - an hour I would've otherwise squandered on mundane toil  
The humdrum reality that my life once seemed so steep;   
I find joy in the beauty of unexpected sights before eyes blind:    
My heart whispers gratitude for a simpler, kinder fate.
